                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>Close of the second stanza of <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_734">Friedrich Rückert</rs>’s poem ‘<ref target="biblio.xml#lit_41">Flügel! Flügel um zu fliegen</ref>’ from the volume <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Liebesfrühling</hi> (1844). The word ‘Flügel’ (wings) in the second line of the quotation does not occur in the original text. See Rückert 1868-1869, vol. 1, p. 494.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>Cf. Rom. 12:12 and Heb. 6:12.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="3" xml:id="note-t-3">
                            

<p>
  Ps. 119:105.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
