                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="7" xml:id="note-t-7">
                            

<p>The etching <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Jan Six reading in front of the window</hi>, 1647 (B285). A later impression by <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1463">Amand-Durand</rs> is to be found in the Van Gogh family estate. <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_1736">Ill. 1736</rs>. (t*1460).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="8" xml:id="note-t-8">
                            

<p><rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1295">Rembrandt</rs>, <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Jan Six</hi>, 1654 (Amsterdam, Six Collection). <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_1737">Ill. 1737</rs>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="9" xml:id="note-t-9">
                            

<p>This probably refers to the engraving after <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1295">Rembrandt</rs>’s <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Portrait of Jan Six</hi> which <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1552">Johann Wilhelm Kaiser</rs> made for the <hi xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" rend="italics">Galerie Six</hi> (1874-1878) (Amsterdam, Rijksprentenkabinet). <rs xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" type="artwork" ref="artwork.xml#ill_1738">Ill. 1738</rs>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
